          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "*💡 CCF works best with REST APIs that support pagination, return JSON, and use standard auth (OAuth2 or API key). No custom code required.*"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Q3",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-HelpQ4a"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Use Codeless Connector Framework (CCF)\r\n\r\nThe CCF allows you to create a custom data connector for Microsoft Sentinel without writing code. Define a JSON configuration that tells Sentinel how to connect to your data source's REST API and ingest data.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Data source must expose a REST API with pagination support\r\n- OAuth2 or API key authentication\r\n- JSON response format\r\n\r\n🔗 [Create a codeless connector](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/create-codeless-connector)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has a REST API (Q3: {Q3}) and CCF is suitable (Q4a: {Q4a}). CCF is the preferred no-code approach for REST API sources — it runs natively in Sentinel with zero infrastructure.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Logs Ingestion API would work but requires custom code to call the API and forward data\r\n- AMA-based methods (CEF/Syslog) don't apply — your source has a REST API, not log streaming\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires REST API with pagination support and JSON responses\r\n- Only supports OAuth2 and API key authentication (no SAML, no client certificate)\r\n- Not suitable for APIs with complex workflows, binary data, or non-standard pagination",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4a",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultCCF"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Use Logs Ingestion API\r\n\r\nThe Logs Ingestion API allows you to send data to a Log Analytics workspace from any REST client. This is the preferred method when a built-in connector or CCF is not available but the source has an API.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE)\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- OAuth/RBAC authentication (Microsoft Entra app registration)\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has a REST API (Q3: {Q3}) but CCF isn't suitable (Q4a: {Q4a}). The Logs Ingestion API gives you full control with custom code to pull data and push it to Sentinel.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- CCF was ruled out — likely the API doesn't support pagination, returns non-JSON, or uses unsupported auth\r\n- AMA-based methods don't apply to REST API sources\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires custom code (Azure Function, Logic App, or script) to call the source API\r\n- You must manage the DCE + DCR + Entra app registration\r\n- Polling frequency and data transformation are your responsibility",
              "style": "success"
            },
            "conditionalVisibilities": [
              {
                "parameterName": "Q3",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "Yes"
              },
              {
                "parameterName": "Q4a",
                "comparison": "isEqualTo",
                "value": "No"
              }
            ],
            "name": "text-ResultLogsAPI"
          },
