            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Azure Monitor Pipeline\r\n\r\nAzure Monitor Pipeline is a containerized, Microsoft-native solution that runs on an Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster. It receives Syslog, CEF, and OTLP telemetry, applies filtering/transformation locally, and forwards data to Azure Monitor.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster with cert-manager extension\r\n- Custom locations enabled on the cluster\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- Log Analytics workspace (with Sentinel for CommonSecurityLog)\r\n\r\n**Key advantages over Logstash:**\r\n- Auto-schematizes to `Syslog` and `CommonSecurityLog` tables\r\n- Persistent local storage survives connectivity loss\r\n- No third-party software to license or maintain\r\n- Built-in TLS/mTLS support\r\n\r\n🔗 [Azure Monitor Pipeline overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/data-collection/pipeline-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), needs preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), and you have an Arc-enabled K8s cluster (Q4c: {Q4c}). Azure Monitor Pipeline is the Microsoft-native choice for centralized log processing.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Logstash would work but requires third-party software licensing and maintenance\r\n- Direct AMA (CEF/Syslog) doesn't provide preprocessing capabilities\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API (you answered No)\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires Arc-enabled Kubernetes cluster with cert-manager extension\r\n- Currently supports Syslog, CEF, and OTLP — other formats may not be supported yet\r\n- You are responsible for operating the Kubernetes environment",
              "style": "success"
            },
