              "json": "### ✅ Logstash with Sentinel Output Plugin\r\n\r\nUse Logstash for data preprocessing, transformation, and enrichment before sending to Microsoft Sentinel. Suitable when no Kubernetes cluster is available.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Logstash instance (existing or new)\r\n- Microsoft Sentinel output plugin (`microsoft-sentinel-log-analytics-logstash-output-plugin`)\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n\r\n🔗 [Connect Logstash to Sentinel](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-logstash-data-connection-rules)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), needs preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), but no Arc-enabled K8s cluster is available (Q4c: {Q4c}). Logstash is the established fallback for preprocessing without Kubernetes.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Azure Monitor Pipeline is preferred but requires K8s (you answered No)\r\n- Direct AMA (CEF/Syslog) doesn't provide preprocessing\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Logstash is open-source but Elastic licensing applies to newer versions\r\n- Requires a dedicated VM or container to run\r\n- You manage plugin updates, pipeline configs, and monitoring yourself",
