            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ CEF via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent (AMA) to collect Common Event Format (CEF) logs. CEF is a standard log format used by many network and security appliances.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Linux log forwarder VM with AMA installed\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) for CEF\r\n- Source device configured to send CEF to the forwarder\r\n\r\n🔗 [Ingest CEF logs with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-cef-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), doesn't need preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), and supports CEF (Q5: {Q5}). AMA with a Linux forwarder is the lightest managed path for CEF data.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Preprocessing solutions (Pipeline/Logstash) are overkill — your data doesn't need transformation\r\n- Syslog via AMA is for non-CEF syslog — CEF is more structured and preferred when available\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires a dedicated Linux forwarder VM with AMA installed\r\n- Forwarder VM sizing affects maximum throughput\r\n- Source device must be configured to send CEF to the forwarder's IP on port 514",
