            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Syslog via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent (AMA) to collect Syslog messages. Suitable for Linux-based appliances and services that emit standard Syslog.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Linux VM with AMA installed (or direct agent on source)\r\n- rsyslog or syslog-ng configured to forward logs\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) for Syslog\r\n\r\n🔗 [Collect Syslog with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-cef-syslog-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), doesn't need preprocessing (Q4b: {Q4b}), doesn't support CEF (Q5: {Q5}), but supports Syslog (Q6: {Q6}). AMA handles standard Syslog natively.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- CEF via AMA was preferred but your source doesn't output CEF format\r\n- Preprocessing solutions are unnecessary — standard Syslog works as-is\r\n- CCF/Logs API require a REST API\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Requires a Linux VM with AMA (or direct agent on source if supported)\r\n- Only standard Syslog facilities and severities are supported\r\n- Custom-formatted syslog messages may need DCR transformations for proper parsing",
