            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Custom Logs v2 — File Upload via AMA\r\n\r\nUse the Azure Monitor Agent to collect log data from text files (CSV, JSON, or custom delimited formats) on Windows or Linux machines.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- AMA installed on the machine with the log files\r\n- Custom table created in Log Analytics workspace\r\n- Data Collection Rule (DCR) with custom log source\r\n\r\n🔗 [Collect custom text logs with AMA](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/connect-custom-logs-ama)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), but exports files (Q7: {Q7}). AMA can tail CSV/JSON files directly from disk.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- All network-based methods (CEF, Syslog, Webhook) don't apply — your source exports files\r\n- Preprocessing isn't needed — the file format is usable as-is\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- AMA must be installed on the machine where files are written\r\n- Requires a custom table in Log Analytics (not a built-in table)\r\n- File rotation and cleanup are your responsibility\r\n- Not suitable for real-time alerting — depends on file write frequency",
