          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ✅ Webhook → Azure Function / Logic App → Logs Ingestion API\r\n\r\nConfigure the data source to push events via webhook to an Azure Function or Logic App, which then forwards data to Sentinel via the Logs Ingestion API.\r\n\r\n**Prerequisites:**\r\n- Azure Function (HTTP trigger) or Logic App (HTTP trigger)\r\n- Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n- Webhook configuration on the source system\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), no file export (Q7: No), but supports webhooks (Q8: {Q8}). Event-driven push via webhook is the most responsive option left.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- All agent-based methods require protocol support your source doesn't have\r\n- File upload is not applicable — your source doesn't export files\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- You need an Azure Function or Logic App to receive and transform the webhook payload\r\n- Webhook endpoints must be internet-accessible (or use private endpoints)\r\n- Retry logic and deduplication are your responsibility\r\n- Cost scales with event volume (Function/Logic App consumption billing)",
