            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### ⚠️ Ad-hoc Upload via Logs Ingestion API (Last Resort)\r\n\r\nWhen no other ingestion method is available, data can be manually or semi-automatically uploaded to Sentinel using the Logs Ingestion API. This is suitable for **low-volume, infrequent** data only.\r\n\r\n**Built on:** Data Collection Endpoint (DCE) + Data Collection Rule (DCR)\r\n\r\n**Key Notes:**\r\n- ❌ Avoid MMA/OMS agent (retired Aug 31, 2024) — use AMA\r\n- ⚠️ HTTP Data Collector API is deprecated (retires Sep 14, 2026)\r\n- Use Logs Ingestion API for all new custom integrations\r\n\r\n🔗 [Logs Ingestion API overview](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/azure-monitor/logs/logs-ingestion-api-overview)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Why this recommendation:**\r\nYour source has no REST API (Q3: {Q3}), no preprocessing needed (Q4b: {Q4b}), no CEF (Q5: {Q5}), no Syslog (Q6: {Q6}), no file export (Q7: No), and no webhooks (Q8: {Q8}). This is the last resort when no automated method is available.\r\n\r\n**Why not the alternatives?**\r\n- Every automated ingestion method has been evaluated and ruled out based on your answers above\r\n\r\n**Constraints:**\r\n- Manual or scripted process — not suitable for high-volume or real-time data\r\n- Requires someone to periodically extract and upload data\r\n- Consider revisiting the tree — can preprocessing (Q4b) unlock a better path via Logstash or Azure Monitor Pipeline?",
