    {
      "type": 12,
      "content": {
        "version": "NotebookGroup/1.0",
        "groupType": "editable",
        "items": [
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "## Installed Data Connectors & Coverage\r\n\r\nThis tab assesses your Sentinel deployment: connector health, data freshness, deployment maturity, and security domain coverage."
            },
            "name": "text-InstalledHeader"
          },
          {
            "type": 1,
            "content": {
              "json": "### 📖 How to Read This Tab\r\n\r\nThis tab assesses your **deployment maturity** — not by counting connectors against the full 600+ catalog (which would always look low), but by classifying your deployment against real-world benchmarks.\r\n\r\n**Deployment Maturity** uses two signals:\r\n- **Installed count** — how many connectors are reporting health data in the last 7 days\r\n- **Domains Covered** — how many of the 11 security domains (Identity, Endpoint, Network, Cloud, Email, Threat Intelligence, etc.) have at least one active connector\r\n\r\n> *\"While Microsoft Sentinel supports 600+ connectors, productive enterprise deployments typically operationalize around 15–40 connectors, scaling higher in mature SOC environments depending on data sources and use-case maturity.\"*\r\n\r\n**What matters more than connector count:**\r\n- ✅ Are **high-value sources** onboarded? (Entra ID, Defender XDR, firewall logs)\r\n- ✅ Are **key security domains** covered? (Identity + Endpoint + Network + Cloud at minimum)\r\n- ✅ Is ingestion **optimized**? (no duplication, no noise, right retention tier)\r\n- ❌ Avoid maximizing connector count — it increases cost and noise without proportional security value\r\n\r\n**Data source:** All health and freshness data comes from the `SentinelHealth` table (last 7 days). Domain coverage is computed by matching installed connectors against the connector catalog watchlist (`Con`).\r\n\r\n**📋 Recommendations** below the summary metrics automatically surfaces coverage gaps (domains with zero or minimal connectors), connector health issues (failures and warnings), and stale data sources. Items are prioritized by severity — address 🔴 High items first.\r\n\r\n🔗 [Best practices for data collection](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/sentinel/best-practices-data)",
              "style": "info"
            },
            "conditionalVisibility": {
              "parameterName": "Help",
              "comparison": "isEqualTo",
              "value": "Yes"
            },
            "name": "text-InstalledHelp"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "let installedRaw = SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| distinct SentinelResourceName;\r\nlet installedCount = toscalar(installedRaw | count);\r\nlet installed = installedRaw\r\n| extend Keys = pack_array(\r\n    tolower(SentinelResourceName),\r\n    tolower(extract(\"^(.+?)-[^-]+$\", 1, SentinelResourceName)),\r\n    replace_regex(tolower(SentinelResourceName), \"connector$\", \"\"))\r\n| mv-expand InstalledKey = Keys to typeof(string)\r\n| where isnotempty(InstalledKey)\r\n| distinct InstalledKey;\r\nlet catalog = _GetWatchlist('Con')\r\n| project\r\n    ConnectorID = column_ifexists(\"Connector ID\", \"\"),\r\n    Domain      = column_ifexists(\"Domain\", \"Other\")\r\n| extend CatalogKey = tolower(ConnectorID);\r\nlet domainsCovered = toscalar(\r\n    catalog\r\n    | join kind=inner installed on $left.CatalogKey == $right.InstalledKey\r\n    | mv-expand SingleDomain = split(Domain, \",\") to typeof(string)\r\n    | extend SingleDomain = trim(\" \", SingleDomain)\r\n    | where SingleDomain != \"Other\"\r\n    | summarize by SingleDomain\r\n    | count\r\n);\r\nlet tier = case(\r\n    installedCount >= 80, \"🟣 Enterprise\",\r\n    installedCount >= 40, \"🟢 Mature SOC\",\r\n    installedCount >= 15, \"🔵 Productive\",\r\n    installedCount >= 5,  \"🟡 Early\",\r\n    \"⚪ Initial\");\r\nprint\r\n    Installed = installedCount,\r\n    Maturity = tier,\r\n    ['Domains Covered'] = strcat(tostring(domainsCovered), ' / 11')",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Deployment Maturity",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "cards",
              "chartSettings": {
                "showMetrics": false
              }
            },
            "customWidth": "33",
            "name": "query-CoverageSummary"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
              "query": "SentinelHealth\r\n| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)\r\n| where SentinelResourceType == \"Data connector\"\r\n| summarize LastStatus = arg_max(TimeGenerated, Status) by SentinelResourceName\r\n| summarize Count = count() by Status\r\n| sort by Count desc",
              "size": 4,
              "title": "Health Summary",
              "timeContext": {
                "durationMs": 604800000
              },
              "queryType": 0,
              "resourceType": "microsoft.operationalinsights/workspaces",
              "visualization": "piechart"
            },
            "customWidth": "33",
            "name": "query-HealthPieChart"
          },
          {
            "type": 3,
            "content": {
              "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
